Leading Summary Paragraph

Describing what I did and Difficulties I encountered

I took my code from homework two and progressively increased the number of files to consider along with the number of directories. Starting with one directory and increasing to five, I found many parts where I ignored missing data and lengths of files that I now needed to consider. I think that this incremental coding and debugging in the beginning and progression of my homework two really set myself up for greater success in the homework four process. While I continued to run into difficulties with longer waiting and running times along with bugs in my code, I think that progressively increasing the number and lengths of files really helped me to complete the full homework. At the end, I was able to successfully run all 2459 directories and files and was proud of the progress I had made and all I had learned since the completion of homework two.
